org.apache.cordova

类 PluginManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.cordova.PluginManager

  • public class PluginManager
extends java.lang.Object
    PluginManager is exposed to JavaScript in the Cordova WebView. Calling native plugin code can be done by calling PluginManager.exec(...) from JavaScript.

      • exec

        public void exec(java.lang.String service,
                 java.lang.String action,
                 java.lang.String callbackId,
                 java.lang.String rawArgs)
        Receives a request for execution and fulfills it by finding the appropriate Java class and calling it's execute method. PluginManager.exec can be used either synchronously or async. In either case, a JSON encoded string is returned that will indicate if any errors have occurred when trying to find or execute the class denoted by the clazz argument.
        参数:
        service - String containing the service to run
        action - String containing the action that the class is supposed to perform. This is passed to the plugin execute method and it is up to the plugin developer how to deal with it.
        callbackId - String containing the id of the callback that is execute in JavaScript if this is an async plugin call.
        rawArgs - An Array literal string containing any arguments needed in the plugin execute method.

      • getPlugin

        public CordovaPlugin getPlugin(java.lang.String service)
        Get the plugin object that implements the service. If the plugin object does not already exist, then create it. If the service doesn't exist, then return null.
        参数:

        返回:
        CordovaPlugin or null

      • onReceivedHttpAuthRequest

        public boolean onReceivedHttpAuthRequest(CordovaWebView view,
                                         ICordovaHttpAuthHandler handler,
                                         java.lang.String host,
                                         java.lang.String realm)
        Called when the system received an HTTP authentication request. Plugins can use the supplied HttpAuthHandler to process this auth challenge.
        参数:
        view - The WebView that is initiating the callback
        handler - The HttpAuthHandler used to set the WebView's response
        host - The host requiring authentication
        realm - The realm for which authentication is required
        返回:
        Returns True if there is a plugin which will resolve this auth challenge, otherwise False

      • onReceivedClientCertRequest

        public boolean onReceivedClientCertRequest(CordovaWebView view,
                                           ICordovaClientCertRequest request)
        Called when he system received an SSL client certificate request. Plugin can use the supplied ClientCertRequest to process this certificate challenge.
        参数:
        view - The WebView that is initiating the callback
        request - The client certificate request
        返回:
        Returns True if plugin will resolve this auth challenge, otherwise False

      • shouldAllowRequest

        public boolean shouldAllowRequest(java.lang.String url)
        Called when the webview is going to request an external resource. This delegates to the installed plugins, and returns true/false for the first plugin to provide a non-null result. If no plugins respond, then the default policy is applied.
        参数:
        url - The URL that is being requested.
        返回:
        Returns true to allow the resource to load, false to block the resource.

      • shouldAllowNavigation

        public boolean shouldAllowNavigation(java.lang.String url)
        Called when the webview is going to change the URL of the loaded content. This delegates to the installed plugins, and returns true/false for the first plugin to provide a non-null result. If no plugins respond, then the default policy is applied.
        参数:
        url - The URL that is being requested.
        返回:
        Returns true to allow the navigation, false to block the navigation.

      • shouldAllowBridgeAccess

        public boolean shouldAllowBridgeAccess(java.lang.String url)
        Called when the webview is requesting the exec() bridge be enabled.

      • shouldOpenExternalUrl

        public java.lang.Boolean shouldOpenExternalUrl(java.lang.String url)
        Called when the webview is going not going to navigate, but may launch an Intent for an URL. This delegates to the installed plugins, and returns true/false for the first plugin to provide a non-null result. If no plugins respond, then the default policy is applied.
        参数:
        url - The URL that is being requested.
        返回:
        Returns true to allow the URL to launch an intent, false to block the intent.

      • onOverrideUrlLoading

        Called when the URL of the webview changes.
        参数:
        url - The URL that is being changed to.
        返回:
        Return false to allow the URL to load, return true to prevent the URL from loading.
